<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Thumpre</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-19 09:27:08</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I bought this from someone cleaning his bank out on TM.<BR>
I'm lvl 21 and currently this hits for a max of 38.  My 2HB is low though - so missing a lot.  I can still solo blue's with it.  It is a sweet weapon,  especially when double attack kicks in.   I have no idea what level it proc's - am guessing upper 30's - 40's.   By that time I will be hunting with enchanters - and the AE proc will force me to move on to some other weapon.  I know when I play my enchanter I get pissed when people cast AE spells that break my mezzes.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: BOHICA</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-21 03:38:53</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This weapon starts to proc at level 30.  At level 30 with 2hb skill maxed you get hits up to 50+ with it.  It's best to have resist/endure Magic on you cause the proc hits you as well. (2 or 3 waves of 75 points damage).  It's great to have if there are 3+ mobs that you are fighting and no enchanter in the group, other than that the proc can be more of a problem to yourself than help.  With resist magic at 50 you will resist about half the damage on average.  It sucks to get hit by your own proc but I have to admit that the proc has saved my butt more than a few times on a multi-mob fight.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
35 Monk - Veeshan</font></td></tr></table>
