<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: a_monk_07</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-29 08:43:36</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>C'mon now, people, has no one else figured out how to very <BR>
effectively USE the proc to its full potential?  I admit it's<BR>
not a wise weapon choice in dungeons, but in the outdoors this<BR>
stick is fantastic!  <BR>
<BR>
Ok, here's what you do, as soon as you see<BR>
the first wave's spell message, take a few steps backward. If<BR>
you're not at the top of the mob's hate list, the mob will stay<BR>
on whoever he's on and stand there to take the waves.  If you ARE<BR>
the focus of the mob's hate, taking these few steps backward will <BR>
get YOU out of the range of the spell but NOT the mob!  His ass<BR>
is still in the edge of the area of effect and the 2nd and 3rd <BR>
waves will hit him but they won't hit you.  True, you still take<BR>
the 1st wave with the mob when it initially procs, but get some<BR>
decent magic resist and you'll shrug it off easily.  I really<BR>
enjoy this staff, I get a nice ratio, only 6.5 weight, (the screen<BR>
shot is outdated), and a welcome possible max of 225 proc damage <BR>
done to my foe.  It also procs VERY often, 2 to 3 times per fight <BR>
is not uncommon with a dexterity of only 115.  Due to the general, <BR>
(wrong), concensus of this item's relative worthlessness, (maybe <BR>
if you just STAND there, and enjoy the pretty lightning along with<BR>
the mob, genius), I got the item for a song.  Until I get a <BR>
stormwood battle staff or better, this'll be mah stick. Hell, in <BR>
the outdoors, I'll still use this one over the stormwood. (Inside <BR>
I don't tempt the fates, I whip out the sage's battle staff I <BR>
currently have when fighting in dungeons.)<BR>
<BR>
"Your skin blisters as lightning rains down upon you."<BR>
YEAH, baby!! </font></td></tr></table>
